N2  - Modern organization theory tells us that an administrator?s attitude toward the satisfaction of the needs of his subordinates is related to the administrator?s personal characteristics. This article presents a statistical analysis of three administrator characteristics ? age, education, and rank ? as determinants of his attitude toward the satisfaction of his subordinates? need for economic security.
